Name: intrahepatic cholestasis of pregnancy 1
Definition: An intrahepatic cholestasis of pregnancy characterized by autosomal dominant inheritance that has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATP8B1 gene on chromosome 18q21.

Name: intrahepatic cholestasis of pregnancy 3
Definition: An intrahepatic cholestasis of pregnancy characterized by autosomal dominant inheritance that has_material_basis_in mutation in the ABCB4 gene on chromosome 7q21.
